cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the identification and quantification of markers in medical images using machine learning techniques. The focus is on retinal optical coherence tomography (OCT) imaging data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) domain. The paper proposes an unsupervised approach for identifying disease marker candidates, which involves training a deep denoising autoencoder and using a one-class support vector machine for anomaly detection. This approach falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves medical image analysis and disease diagnosis, which falls under the sub-categories of medical imaging (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
